eshmun.modelchecker

Class AbstractModelChecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • eshmun.modelchecker.AbstractModelChecker
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    KripkeModelChecker

    public abstract class AbstractModelChecker
extends java.lang.Object
    This class defines an abstract model checker, implementing sub classes may implement a variety of specific algorithms.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Kinan Dak Al Bab
    See Also:
    Visitable, AbstractModelChecker, AbstractExpression, AbstractStructure

    • Method Detail

      • visit

        protected boolean visit(AbstractExpression specifications,
                        AbstractState state,
                        int index)
        Calls the right visit method and pass it the parameters depending on the type of the expression.
        Parameters:
        specifications - the specifications.
        state - the state to start from.
        index - the remaining state to traverse before reaching total number of states.
        Returns:
        the result of the (partial) modelChecking of state against the specifications with the index, this result is complete when the state is the start state and specifications are the entire specs.

      • run

        public abstract boolean run(AbstractExpression specifications)
        Model-checks a structure against CTL specifications, the structure should be provided elsewhere.

        This method should be overridden in the concrete model checker.

        Parameters:
        specifications - CTL specifications to model-check against.
        Returns:
        true if the structure satisfies the specifications, false otherwise.
